div.p: Color Semantics Red = privilege-change / danger path Blue = data pushed onto stack Green = success / return path Purple = hardware-read metadata / TSS Gray = CPU internal state

text.tspan: loaded via selector 0x28 in TR register

div.p: INT 0x80 asm mov eax, 4 ; SYS_WRITE mov ebx, 1 ; fd=stdout mov ecx, buf ; ptr mov edx, len ; count int 0x80 ; software interrupt
Key rule: ESP0 must be updated on every context switch to the new process's kernel_stack_top. Stale ESP0 kernel stack corruption on next ring transition.
DPL=3 user code may invoke via int 0x80 type=trap IF not cleared, kernel stays interruptible selector=0x08 handler runs in kernel code segment

g.text: 0xBFFFFEFC user ESP (user stack ptr before INT)
0x00401237 user EIP (return addr: instr after INT)
0x00000000 fake error code (int gate, no err)
EDI ESI EBP ESP EBX EDX ECX EAX
DS ES FS GS (saved before kernel segs loaded)
ESP passed to C handler as 'interrupt_frame *'

div.p: iret pop order (return path): EIP CS EFLAGS (CS.RPL=3 detected also pops:) ESP SS switch back to user stack
isr_128: (NASM) asm push dword 0 ; fake err_code push dword 128 ; int_no jmp isr_common_stub

isr_common_stub: asm pusha ; save EDI,ESI,EBP,ESP,EBX,EDX,ECX,EAX push ds / es / fs / gs mov ax, 0x10 ; load kernel data segments mov ds/es/fs/gs, ax push esp ; interrupt_frame * arg call interrupt_dispatch add esp, 4 pop gs/fs/es/ds popa add esp, 8 ; remove int_no + err_code iretd ; THE RETURN INSTRUCTION

iretd execution (hardware): Step Pop EIP 0x00401237 (user return addr) Step Pop CS 0x0000001B (RPL=3 detected!) Step Pop EFLAGS 0x00000202 (IF=1 restored) CS.RPL(3) > CPL(0) privilege change on return Step Pop ESP 0xBFFFFEFC (user stack ptr) Step Pop SS 0x00000023 (user stack seg) CPU switches active stack to user stack CPL becomes 3 (from CS bits 0-1) Execution resumes at 0x00401237 in ring 3 EAX = sys_write return value (bytes written)
Stack contents (before INT) 0xBFFFF000 ... user local vars ... 0xBFFFFFF0 ... return addr to caller ... ESP_user = 0xBFFFFEFC
